==Literary accounts==
Sir Henry Rider Haggard&#x27;s novels &quot;Nada the Lily&quot; and &quot;Marie&quot; include versions of some events in Dingane&#x27;s life, as does Bertram Mitford&#x27;s 1898 novel &quot;The Induna&#x27;s Wife.&quot;

